# Claude Code Documentation Auto-Sync Cron Configuration
#
# Add this to your crontab to automatically sync documentation updates
# Run: crontab -e
# Then add one of the following lines (uncomment the one you want)
#

# Option 1: Sync every 6 hours (matches repository update schedule)
0 */6 * * * cd /path/to/claude-code-docs && ./auto-sync/auto-sync.sh --quiet

# Option 2: Sync every hour (more frequent checks)
0 * * * * cd /path/to/claude-code-docs && ./auto-sync/auto-sync.sh --quiet

# Option 3: Sync twice daily (morning and evening)
0 9,18 * * * cd /path/to/claude-code-docs && ./auto-sync/auto-sync.sh --quiet

# Option 4: Sync once daily at 3 AM
0 3 * * * cd /path/to/claude-code-docs && ./auto-sync/auto-sync.sh --quiet

# Option 5: Check for updates every 30 minutes, only sync if needed
*/30 * * * * cd /path/to/claude-code-docs && ./auto-sync/check-updates.sh && ./auto-sync/auto-sync.sh --quiet

#
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
#
# 1. Replace /path/to/claude-code-docs with your actual repository path
# 2. The --quiet flag suppresses output (logs still written to auto-sync/sync.log)
# 3. Make sure you have git credentials configured for the repository
# 4. To view logs: tail -f /path/to/claude-code-docs/auto-sync/sync.log
# 5. To disable: run 'crontab -e' and comment out or remove the line
#
# For macOS users:
# - Cron may require Full Disk Access permission in System Settings
# - Alternatively, consider using launchd for better macOS integration
#